The matching of source blocks to holes is primarily determined by the dimensions of the holes and blocks. Multiple source blocks of the same color can combine to fill a larger hole (e.g., two 3x2 blocks filling a 6x2 hole, or two 2x3 blocks filling a 2x6 hole). The grey (5) pixels appear to be markers or distractors and are removed in the output.

        *   Hole B: 1x1 at Row 2, Col 11.
        *   Hole C: 1x3 at Rows 3-5, Col 8.
    *   **Teal Container:** Located roughly at Rows 7-17, Cols 17-24.
        *   Hole D: 6x1 at Row 7, Cols 18-23.
        *   Hole E: 1x4 at Rows 8-11, Col 23.
        *   Hole F: 2x6 at Rows 11-16, Cols 19-20.
        *   Hole G: 2x2 at Rows 14-15, Cols 22-23.
